Additionally, if you are located in the EEA, we note that we are generally processing your information in order to fulfill contracts we might have with you (for example if you make an appointment through the service), or otherwise to pursue our legitimate business interests listed above, unless we are required by law to obtain your consent for a particular processing operation.
As you visit, or browse the Setster websites, we collect information about the device and browser you use, your network connection, your IP address, and information about the cookies installed on your device.
California law requires us to disclose certain information regarding the categories of personal information we collect.
For each category of information, we collect data from a variety of sources, including directly from you, from your devices, from your social media profiles, and/or from third party providers.
We also may use this information to provide you with advertising or marketing.
We also use this information to improve our Services.
We also use this information to make sure that we comply with legal requirements.
We collect the information to provide you with services, protect our customers and ourselves (including the services), and to improve the services.
We collect this information when you use or access a booking page that uses our Services, such as when you visit a Customer's site, book an appointment or fill a contact form on a Customer's site that is using our Service.
We collect this information when you visit the Setster websites, use Services offered on our websites or engage with us either by email, web form, instant message, phone, or post content on or through our websites (including forums, blogs and via any Messaging Feature).
We may also share your information in the following circumstances:
We use this information to give you access to and improve our Services and to make our platform interface easier to use.
We use this information to provide our Customers with the Services, including supporting and processing appointments, authentication, and payments.
We use this information to provide you with our Services and so that you can book appointments and use the features provided within the Service.
We use this information to provide you with our Services; for example, to confirm your identity, create your Setster Service account, contact you, provide you with advertising and marketing, and invoice you.
We use this information to verify your account, to provide and enhance our Services (including supporting or servicing your account, if applicable), and answer any questions you may have regarding our Services.
